President Biden delivered a speech in Wilkes-Barre, Pennsylvania, where he discussed his crime plan and called for increased support for law enforcement. He emphasized the need to fund the police and highlighted the importance of community policing. He also addressed the issue of gun violence and called for a ban on assault weapons, stating that it is not about taking away guns from responsible gun owners. He stressed the need for common-sense gun laws and mentioned the importance of preventing crime through programs that provide job opportunities and support for at-risk youth. The President also condemned the violence and insurrection at the Capitol on January 6th, and criticized those who defend it. He called for unity and bipartisan cooperation in addressing the challenges facing the country.